# Rust Development Rules

## Code Style and Structure
- Follow the official Rust style guide (rustfmt conventions)
- Use idiomatic Rust patterns and idioms
- Embrace Rust's ownership and borrowing system
- Prefer immutable variables (`let`) over mutable ones (`let mut`)
- Use meaningful and descriptive names for variables, functions, and types
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Organize code into modules logically
- Use proper visibility modifiers (pub, pub(crate), etc.)